OL,3,COlympians and Paralympians back plan
OL,4,Cfor north of England games bid
OL,6,FMore than 40 figures from across
OL,7,FBritish sport have now signed a joint
OL,8,Fstatement of support for a North of
OL,9,FEngland Games.
OL,11,FThe statement has attracted support
OL,12,Ffrom sporting names including Dame
OL,13,FLaura Kenny, Sir Jason Kenny, Dame
OL,14,FSarah Storey, Britain's most
OL,15,Fsuccessful Paralympian, double Olympic
OL,16,Fchampion Tom Pidcock, Ed Clancy,
OL,17,Fgymnast Beth Tweddle, and Steve Cram.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1782220722
OL,3,COlympians and Paralympians back plan
OL,4,Cfor north of England games bid
OL,6,FThey are joined by Sir Brendan Foster,
OL,7,Ffounder of the Great North Run,
OL,8,FOlympic medallists Laura Weightman and
OL,9,FMarc Scott, Paralympic medallists
OL,10,FSusie Rodgers, Krysten Coombs and Rob
OL,11,FDavies, and a new generation of
OL,12,Fathletes such as Paris 2024 Paralympic
OL,13,Fchampion Poppy Maskill.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/9
